I'm building a Report Onboarding configuration editor. 
The UI must strictly follow the SALT design system 
(JPMorgan's open-source React component library).

## Stack
- React + TypeScript
- SALT Design System (@salt-ds/core, @salt-ds/lab, @salt-ds/icons)
- No custom CSS except layout grid — every interactive element 
  must be a SALT component

## Layout
Two-pane layout, 240px left / flex-1 right:
- Left: NavigationItem tree (saltNavigationItem) for the config 
  hierarchy — ResourceGroup → Resources[] → Views[] → Segments[]
- Right: context-sensitive form panel for the selected node

## Component mapping (enforce these strictly)
- Tree nodes          → SaltNavigationItem with SaltIcon
- All text inputs     → SaltInput
- Dropdowns           → SaltDropdown or SaltComboBox
- Date fields         → SaltDatePicker
- Tabs per node       → SaltTabBar + SaltTab
- Filter rows         → SaltStackLayout with SaltInput + SaltButton
- Save/action buttons → SaltButton (variant="cta" for primary)
- Status badges       → SaltPill
- Section headings    → SaltText variant="label"
- Raw JSON toggle     → SaltSwitch
- JSON textarea       → SaltFormField wrapping a plain <textarea> 
                        with SALT form field styling
- Breadcrumb          → SaltBreadcrumb

