## Node types and their tabs
ResourceGroup tabs: Identity | Group config | Parameters | Filters
Resource tabs:      Identity | Filters | Views
View tabs:          Identity | View config | Segments  
Segment tabs:       Identity | Segment config

## Behaviour rules
1. Selecting a tree node updates the right panel — no page 
   navigation, this is a single-page editor
2. Raw JSON toggle shows the selected node's JSON only, 
   not the full config
3. Adding a child node (view to resource, segment to view) 
   opens a SaltDialog with a minimal creation form
4. Filters are an editable array — add/remove rows inline
5. Config fields (viewConfig, segmentConfig) are dynamic 
   key-value pairs — render as editable rows, not hardcoded fields
6. Unsaved changes show a SaltPill "Unsaved" in the header
7. Validation: required fields (id, name) block save with 
   SaltFormField validationStatus="error"

## What NOT to do
- Do not use plain HTML inputs, divs styled as buttons, 
  or custom color variables
- Do not invent a component that SALT already has
- Do not hardcode the config shape — the right panel must 
  render dynamically from the node's data
